item.title: Whoopi Goldberg Apologizes For Using The Term "Gypped" On 'The View'
item.description: Whoopi Goldberg has now apologized for a term she used on The View which offended people of Romani heritage. On Wednesday (March 15), Goldberg got into a discussion about Donald Trump and Stormy Daniels, whereas the 67-year-old said, “The people who still believe that he [Trump] got, you know, gypped somehow in the election…” The word, which is commonly used as a synonym for someone getting cheated or deceived, is also derived from a slur used against the Romani, or Roma, people.
